  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "International Organization for Migration (IOM) will work with Association of  Medical Doctors, Asia (AMDA) in seven camps in the south east part of Nepal to  provide tuberculosis (TB) screening and treatment for Bhutanese refugees.  Currently TB screening and treatment protocol implemented in the camps differs  from the protocol of the resettlement countries. The purpose of this project is  to ensure that the refugees who apply for resettlement and those who have not  yet entered resettlement programmes receive the same effective TB diagnosis and  treatment."
    },
    "ne": null
